    <p>
        Pharmacy Marts is committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information.
        This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose information when you use our
        B2B solution for pharmacies in Egypt.
    </p>

    <p>
        By accessing or using the service, you agree to the terms and conditions of this Privacy Policy.
        If you do not agree with any part of this policy, please do not use the service.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information when you use Pharmacy Marts:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number.</li>
        <li><strong>Pharmacy information:</strong> Pharmacy name, address, and type (individual / chain).</li>
        <li><strong>Order information:</strong> Selected products, quantities, and prices.</li>
        <li>
            <strong>Technical information:</strong> Browser type, device information,
            and approximate location for analytics.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
    <p>We may use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To simulate placing and managing pharmacy orders inside this training project.</li>
        <li>To provide, operate, and maintain the service.</li>
        <li>To communicate with you and respond to your inquiries.</li>
        <li>To personalize and improve your experience with the service.</li>
        <li>To monitor and analyze usage in order to improve our products and services.</li>
        <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues, abuse, or fraud.</li>
        <li>To comply with applicable legal and regulatory obligations (where relevant).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data sharing and disclosure</h2>
    <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal data. In this demo project, data is not shared with
        external third parties such as advertisers. Limited access may be given to instructors or
        developers supervising the training for debugging and improvement purposes only.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Data retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>
        We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined
        in this Privacy Policy or as required by applicable law. Because this is a training environment,
        data may be reset or cleared periodically as part of the learning process.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Security</h2>
    <p>
        We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information from
        unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no system can be guaranteed
        to be 100% secure, especially in a demo or training environment, so please avoid entering
        highly sensitive personal or medical data.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Important medical note</h2>
    <p>
        The information on this website is for training and educational purposes only.
        It is <strong>not</strong> a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
        Always consult a licensed doctor or pharmacist before taking any medication or
        making decisions about your health.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, practices, or data handling within this
        project, please contact us at:
        <a href="mailto:help@pharmacymarts.com">help@pharmacymarts.com</a>.
    </p>
